The paper discusses the development of low-complexity iterative thresholding algorithms for reconstructing sparse signals from a small set of linear measurements, which is a problem in compressed sensing. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the derivation of the algorithms from standard sum-product belief propagation, which falls under cs.SP (Signal Processing). The paper also mentions extensions of the original framework, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
